# AI Cost Awareness

## Budget Target

**Goal: < $24/month total AI spend** (cloud + local infrastructure).

- Mac Studio M4 Max local inference: ~$0/API call (electricity only, ~$10/mo)
- Anthropic cloud budget: `IRON_BUDGET_LIMIT` per session (default $15)
- Monthly cloud cap: set in billing dashboard

## Cost Model

| Tier | Model | Cost | Use When |
|---|---|---|---|
| Free | `qwen2.5-coder:7b` (local) | $0 | Classification, routing, task tagging |
| Free | `qwen2.5-coder:14b` (local) | $0 | YAML, lightweight code, config |
| Free | `qwen2.5-coder:32b` (local) | $0 | Full PR review pass 1, code gen |
| Economy | `claude-3-haiku` | ~$0.001 | Cloud fallback for classification |
| Standard | `claude-sonnet-4` | ~$0.01 | Standard code analysis, test gen |
| Premium | `claude-opus-4` | ~$0.10 | PR review pass 2, architecture, security |

## When AI Is Worth Credits

- Complex code reviews on new Terraform modules or security-sensitive code
- Schema discovery for new data sources (source onboarding agent)
- Generating initial dbt models from scratch (transform copilot)
- Terraform plan risk analysis before production deployments
- Incident root cause analysis on pipeline failures
- PII detection and governance classification
- Agent plan() phase — plan quality determines implementation quality

## When to Use Local (Mac Studio / vLLM)

Default to local for:
- PR review pass 1 (every PR, zero cloud cost)
- Routine code analysis and linting advice
- YAML config generation
- Task classification and routing decisions
- Test generation for well-understood code

Local fallback is transparent — set `IRON_USE_LOCAL_LLMS=true` and the router handles it.

## When NOT to Use Cloud AI

- Routine linting — use `ruff`, `sqlfluff`, `terraform fmt`
- Simple formatting fixes — use `ruff format`
- Re-reviewing unchanged code — cache hit, zero cost
- Commit message validation — regex pre-commit hook
- Documentation that can be templated from YAML

## Cost-Saving Patterns in Code

```python
from ironrecall_core.llm import LLMRouter, ModelTier

router = LLMRouter()

# Prefer local for standard tasks
response = router.call(prompt, tier=ModelTier.STANDARD, prefer_local=True)

# Cache identical prompts automatically — SHA-256 hash key
# Identical input → cached response → $0 cost

# Batch files into a single call when possible
response = router.call(batch_prompt, tier=ModelTier.STANDARD, max_tokens=2048)

# All agents must call self._track_usage() after each API call
# Usage logged to ~/.iron/ai-usage.log
```

## Monitoring

```bash
ironpilot ai-usage          # Show cumulative spend this session
ironpilot ai-usage --month  # Show month-to-date spend
```

Budget gate: if `IRON_BUDGET_LIMIT` is exceeded, agents pause and ask for confirmation.
